\usepackage{amssymb}
\usepackage{amsbsy}
\usepackage{upgreek}
\usepackage{mathrsfs}
\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
\begin{document}
$g = 2$\end{document} resonance frequency of dark electrons without graphene, indicative of the electron spins. Notably, the amplitude of this resonance dip significantly diminished upon graphene coverage, suggesting a suppression of the detected surface electron signal from the interface.

